comment_text: I love the size, the design, and having the Snapdragon SoC in Europe is great. The S25 is the only small sized flagship available right now. But Samsung phoned it in several key areas. Namely, the S25 has no UWB, which will become increasingly important. The camera sensors on it are outdated. It does not use a silicon-carbon battery which increases capacity. Finally, it still starts at 128GB. Besides price gauging on the 256GB variant, the carriers will only bother stocking the 128GB variant, with no 256GB option.
